GitHub is a website developers use to store code, save versions of code, work with teams, review changes, track tasks, and deploy projects.



Git is the tool that tracks changes on your computer. GitHub is the website where your Git projects live online. 


When you make a coding project, GitHub lets you:

  Save your code online

  Go back to older versions

  Work on features without breaking the main project

  Show your work to employers / Work with other developers


